        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(browser): move ssrf-runtime-internal exports to public ssrf-runti…",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\r\ncloses #96639\r\nFixes the browser plugin lazy-load crash where `openclaw browser status` and any browser agent tool fail with:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPackage subpath './plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime-internal' is not defined by \"exports\"\r\nin openclaw/package.json imported from openclaw\\dist\\cdp.helpers-B5T7VOSu.js\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\n\r\n`registerManagedProxyBrowserCdpBypass` and `fetchConfiguredLocalOriginWithSsrFGuard` were only exported from the private `openclaw/plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime-internal` subpath. Export both functions from the public `openclaw/plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime` path and update consumer imports.\r\n\r\n## What Changed\r\n\r\n9 files, +10/−15 lines. No `package.json` or config changes.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n\r\nEnvironment: Linux x64, Node v22.19.0, Chromium 148.\r\n\r\n### Before (origin/main) — confirmed broken\r\n\r\n```text\r\n# dist file excluded from package\r\n$ ls dist/plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime-internal.js\r\nFILE NOT FOUND\r\n\r\n# Node.js exports map rejects the import\r\n$ node -e \"import('openclaw/plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime-internal')\"\r\nError: Package subpath './plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime-internal' is not defined by \"exports\"\r\n\r\n# Two functions NOT in public ssrf-runtime\r\n$ node --import tsx -e \"\r\nconst mod = await import('openclaw/plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime');\r\nconsole.log('registerManagedProxyBrowserCdpBypass:', typeof mod.registerManagedProxyBrowserCdpBypass);\r\nconsole.log('fetchConfiguredLocalOriginWithSsrFGuard:', typeof mod.fetchConfiguredLocalOriginWithSsrFGuard);\r\n\"\r\nregisterManagedProxyBrowserCdpBypass: undefined\r\nfetchConfiguredLocalOriginWithSsrFGuard: undefined\r\n```\r\n\r\n### After (fix/browser-ssrf-runtime-import) — confirmed fixed\r\n\r\n```text\r\n# Both functions importable from public ssrf-runtime\r\n$ node --import tsx -e \"\r\nconst mod = await import('openclaw/plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime');\r\nconsole.log('registerManagedProxyBrowserCdpBypass:', typeof mod.registerManagedProxyBrowserCdpBypass);\r\nconsole.log('fetchConfiguredLocalOriginWithSsrFGuard:', typeof mod.fetchConfiguredLocalOriginWithSsrFGuard);\r\n\"\r\nregisterManagedProxyBrowserCdpBypass: function\r\nfetchConfiguredLocalOriginWithSsrFGuard: function\r\n\r\n# E2E: browser plugin lazy-loads, gateway returns full status\r\n$ pnpm build && pnpm openclaw gateway start && pnpm openclaw browser status\r\nprofile:          openclaw\r\nenabled:          true\r\ntransport:        cdp\r\ncdpUrl:           http://127.0.0.1:18800\r\ndetectedBrowser:  chrome\r\ndetectedPath:     /usr/bin/google-chrome-stable\r\nEXIT: 0\r\n\r\n# Private subpath infrastructure unchanged\r\n$ grep \"!dist/plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime-internal\" package.json\r\n\"!dist/plugin-sdk/ssrf-runtime-internal.js\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Unit tests\r\n\r\n| Test | Result |\r\n|------|--------|\r\n| ollama embedding-provider (25) | 25/25 passed |\r\n| browser cdp-proxy-bypass (28) | 27/28 (1 pre-existing env issue) |\r\n| contract guardrail (21) | 21/21 passed |\r\n| surface-report --check | exit 0 |\r\n\r\n### Test conclusion\r\n\r\n| Check | Before (origin/main) | After (fix) |\r\n|-------|---------------------|-------------|\r\n| Public import of both functions | `undefined` | `function` |\r\n| `openclaw browser status` | — | exit 0, full output |\r\n| Unit tests | — | 73/74 passed |\r\n| Private dist exclusion | unchanged | unchanged |\r\n\r\n## Root Cause\r\n\r\n`registerManagedProxyBrowserCdpBypass` (`a37ebb2d49`) and `fetchConfiguredLocalOriginWithSsrFGuard` (`fd2a9adbe6`) were placed in the private `ssrf-runtime-internal` module. Its dist artifact was excluded via `!dist/` (added by `2229122077`) and it had no `package.json` exports entry. Node.js native module resolution rejected the import at runtime.\r\n",
        "branch": "fix/browser-ssrf-runtime-import",
